review_blob: On tap @ The Rover. New recipe on this one. Not so "green" as I remeber it last year. A bigger maltyness but still very drinkable. Clear golden colour. Oppigrds delivers as always

On tap @ Bishops Arms Vsters. Pours black with nice "latte-look-alike" head. Aroma of coffe, chocolate and grassy hops. Taste is alot of coffee, brown sugar, dark chocolate and fruits. And that grassy hop again. Pretty bitter in the aftertaste but not harsh. Really liked this one!
Absolutly fantastic. Proud to have tried them all! Dark, rich, chocolate, raisins. Great smell, fantastic taste. One of the best I have ever tried!
